subSubSection.paragraph:
Dist.: occurring from eastern mainland Spain to Croatia, including France, Italy, Switzerland, Germany, Austria and Slovenia (
Beuk & Pape 2013
; 
Kehlmaier 2021
). 
SPAIN
: Cabrils {
41°31’N
2°22’E
}; 
FRANCE
: 
type
was assigned to occur in “southern France”, other cited locations are Bouches-du-Rhône, La Ciotat {
43°10’N
5°36’E
}, Nantes [
47°14’19.62’’N
1°33’17.60’’E
], Les Eyzeis-de-Tayac-Sireuil {
44°56’N
1°02’E
}, Les Grandes Landes {
45°29’N
1°01’E
} and Charnay {
45°53’N
4°39’E
}. 
ITALY
: the species occurs in the northern half of the mainland and 
Sardinia
(
Kehlmaier 2021
); there is also a report from Giglia Island {
42°21’N
10°53’E
}; historic records from southern Italy including 
Sardinia
and 
Sicily
need to be re-evaluated; 
AUSTRIA
: reported from Linz {
48°17’N
14°18’E
}; 
CROATIA
: reported from Rovinj {
45°04’N
13°40’E
}, Premantura {
44°47’N
13°54’E
}, Lošinj {
44°40’N
14°22’E
}, Podaca {
43°08’N
17°19’E
} 
Dubrovnik-Neretva
, Mljet {
42°44’N
17°32’E
} and Baška Voda {
44°58’N
14°47’E
}; 
SLOVENIA
: from Osp {
45°34’N
13°51’E
}, 
Piran
{
45°31’N
13°34’E
} and Fiesta {
45°31’N
13°34’E
}; 
SWITZERLAND
: from Montorge (
Valais
) {
46°13’N
7°20’E
}; 
GERMANY
: Weil am Rhein, gravel pit Käppelin [
47°35’08.3’’N
7°37’52.6’’E
]. Historic records from Bulgaria and Greece need to be re-evaluated.

